-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/uae-m1-money-supply-grows-annual-13-percent-in-june-correct-.html
(Corrects M3 figure in first paragraph.)  United Arab Emiratesâ€™ M3  money
supply , an indicator of future inflation, increased 12.4 percent
in June from a year earlier, according to data e-mailed by the
central bank today.  M2 money supply, which includes time and savings deposits,
increased 12.5 percent from the previous year, the central bank
said. M1 supply growth, the narrowest measure, climbed 13
percent. M3 money supply includes demand deposits and currency
outside banks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
